{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Qualitative research involves careful consideration of ethical principles (Webster et al., 2013).",
    "To ensure informed consent, participants were fully briefed on the study's nature, purpose, and potential risks, adhering to Regulation 2016/679.",
    "To maintain anonymity and confidentiality, interview details were protected through encryption and password security.",
    "To address power imbalances in the researcher-participant relationship, a conducive environment for interviews was created (Ganga & Scott, 2006).",
    "The study prioritised the potential impact on participants, providing them with sufficient time to think through their responses and offering support as needed."
  ],
